On Wed, 17 Nov 2004 22:20:55 -0000, Kenneth Stanley
<kstanley@...> wrote:
> 
> 
> Man, I just gotta say, this is a really cool demo.  I think what's
> so compelling about it is that you are watching the eye "thinking."
> Hopefully if you get a paper accepted you'll get a chance to show
> this demo.  I think it would get a really good reaction.

Thanks...we hope so too.  Right now we're wrangling with the NIST
Special Database 4, a database of preclassified fingerprint images
that's a standard benchmark in a lot of the literature.  It's from
1992, and the images are compressed and stored in a proprietary
format, and the software is clunky and difficult to compile,
and...welcome to the world of research. :)

We hope that we can get some good work done over the next month, and
evolve the networks for a system that's able to generalize and perform
well on a large test set.

We'll keep you guys posted on our progress.

Derek
